# Social Media Brand — secrets allowlist
# Copy to .env (gitignored) and fill in real values. Platform encrypts on import.
# See ../SECRETS_MATRIX.md for the rationale of this scope.
#
# Social Media Brand drafts content and schedules posts via PRs / draft queues.
# It does NOT publish directly to X or LinkedIn — Marketing Lead is the SOLE
# PUBLISHER (see SECRETS_MATRIX.md).
#
# This allowlist documents the role-owned integrations accepted by the current
# template-import secret flow. SCM credentials are platform-managed and do not
# belong in this file.

# Model authentication uses the platform token flow by default. Add an optional
# BYOK value only when the selected runtime/model explicitly declares it.

# SCM identity is provisioned per workspace by the platform. Do not place a
# personal access token in this file; the role receives only its assigned
# Gitea repository permissions.
